<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-66F6D96C-56FF-40FF-8231-3AF2535E41F9" version="2" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-66F6D96C-56FF-40FF-8231-3AF2535E41F9" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title "> Extended installation wizard behavior (R4.3.x.x)</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="M148553-B105"><p class="- topic/p ">The installation wizard will guide the configuration and calibration actions of the printer. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Beginning with Release 4.3, a fresh installation of the printer at a customer's location will be guided by a new extended installation wizard. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">This wizard is designed to streamline and automate the configuration and SDS calibration actions, ensuring a smooth and error-free installation process. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">To maintain the installation's integrity, the controller will not authorize any jobs until the wizard completes its tasks. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The installation wizard will persistently remain active until it successfully finishes its operations. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">See video: 
<xref class="- topic/xref " format="html" href="http://localhost:20346/VIDEO00394EN.US/video10/index.html" scope="external"><?ditaot usertext?>Introducing R4.3.x.x (service version)</xref> 
</p></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Installation</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><section id="GUID-A8F12881-2DD2-4E11-8AAC-5015EE0A2859" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "/></section><section id="SECTION_F0C46BBCD2F642BC89CFC563F50CE61E" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Layout</title><fig id="GUID-99B6FB1F-31D7-40B9-B4E5-5333FF490D60" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-5444B724-60CC-4771-826D-731F95ECC401-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-5444B724-60CC-4771-826D-731F95ECC401-low.png"/></fig><table id="GUID-E60D5B5E-51AC-4670-BD5E-EBE4CA064F60" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="5*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="95*" class="- topic/colspec "/><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Status field, indicating engine activity and status. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Title of a group of actions in the wizard. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Title of the sub step in a group in the wizard 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">4 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Indication on the action that is necessary or description of the setting to be made. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">5 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Setting selection field, sometimes 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">6 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Progress indication of the step level. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">7 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Action buttons; highlighted actions can be selected. 
</p><fig id="GUID-DB9B2D23-DE07-4746-ADC0-8C6CAF1496FB" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-9C40E37B-4285-4515-AD5A-6733F47A8A9C-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-9C40E37B-4285-4515-AD5A-6733F47A8A9C-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">Cancel the wizard 
</p><fig id="GUID-65D2D620-6204-490A-B769-A670CF9BE800" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-E5EB93E4-EB75-4326-8132-86BC98503766-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-E5EB93E4-EB75-4326-8132-86BC98503766-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">Go back to the previous step 
</p><fig id="GUID-A574744C-D71F-491F-9C61-4820EA98401B" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-605DF1BD-E946-405A-9F7A-055890601E47-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-605DF1BD-E946-405A-9F7A-055890601E47-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">Continue with next step 
</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-5C6D6614-A771-4DC4-AC96-746E8EF5DF77" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Usage of the wizard</title></section><section id="GUID-E11CE34A-3486-4D60-A719-1112CB09B0AE" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "/><p class="- topic/p ">During the execution of the wizard the system status field canfield can turn red and indicate “Operator intervention required”. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> E.g. 
</p><fig id="GUID-66CABA46-3A5F-434B-80F2-D7C0F192234E" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-1784E8FB-01DF-42FA-AC52-0ECDC7E5A08A-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-1784E8FB-01DF-42FA-AC52-0ECDC7E5A08A-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p "> If the red status bar appears, exit the wizard by pressing the Cancel button to address the highlighted issues. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">This allows for resolution before returning to the wizard to resume the installation process. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> The primary aim is to prevent engine status from obstructing overall progress. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The resolution approach might vary across installations as these scenarios aren't fixed and can differ. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Upon resuming the wizard, it's possible to revisit a previously completed step. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">This happens because certain steps are grouped, and if a group remains incomplete, it necessitates redoing the entire set of tasks within that group. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Specific handling details aren't provided, only a general overview is given. 
</p></section><section id="GUID-0C0665D7-F8CB-4D12-9AC5-EFFEBB5834F1" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Issues to be resolved</title><p class="- topic/p "> In 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">order of priority</b> (highest is first item to solve) 
</p><table id="GUID-006287FD-9F90-4A00-8460-A5EAE62ACAA9" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="1.00*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="5.50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Where 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Screenshot, actions and remarks 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Main error screen 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> The popup will continue appearing until every printhead is filled with ink. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Before pressing the OK button, ensure to verify the valves. 
</p><fig id="GUID-3E010EA6-A5D4-4104-8857-03DA2E3CE0A4" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-A992B28A-B056-4DD0-8DDD-6FCCF7D8B0DE-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-A992B28A-B056-4DD0-8DDD-6FCCF7D8B0DE-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Tools tile 
</p><fig id="GUID-9491BFBD-9209-4DD5-8894-3E527EDB2C1B" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-570F9D22-E4EB-4E14-A534-7F6F581E757D-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-570F9D22-E4EB-4E14-A534-7F6F581E757D-low.png"/></fig></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> If the maintenance tray isn't positioned correctly, this notification will display. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> It serves to prevent the engine from initiating tasks such as loading ink, media, and other necessary initializations. 
</p><fig id="GUID-0056D70D-E02E-41CE-B243-39D12FEED5E7" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-E80C7F85-8282-4766-A418-7D2B4378B8A5-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-E80C7F85-8282-4766-A418-7D2B4378B8A5-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Tools tile 
</p><fig id="GUID-AAE3F011-85DD-4582-A126-C306E91B3D20" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-570F9D22-E4EB-4E14-A534-7F6F581E757D-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-570F9D22-E4EB-4E14-A534-7F6F581E757D-low.png"/></fig></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The tissue cassette isn't properly positioned, this notification will appear. Its purpose is to halt the engine from performing tasks like loading ink, media, and other essential initializations. 
</p><fig id="GUID-A9DFB042-C8C5-4D5F-BEFF-3217A5D23F9D" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-2D725A4E-9925-480B-8A8E-916EE9DDAB0E-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-2D725A4E-9925-480B-8A8E-916EE9DDAB0E-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Inks tile 
</p><fig id="GUID-CD41B5A1-3461-430D-8991-D5ECEEF05336" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-65B0E8B1-E619-4657-A614-FF348185A128-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-65B0E8B1-E619-4657-A614-FF348185A128-low.png"/></fig></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">If any of the ink jars becomeis empty, this message will be displayed. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Refill the jars following the instructions provided in the user guide. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">If the waste tray or tissue cassette isn't positioned correctly, the LEDs on the ink loading station won't illuminate, and the bottles won't be detected. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> It's crucial to ensure proper placement of both the waste tray and tissue cassette. 
</p><fig id="GUID-CB942DF3-CF2F-42FB-A9F3-D8D77F1586FF" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-8350C856-38BA-4B5B-BEFF-399B5586B043-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-8350C856-38BA-4B5B-BEFF-399B5586B043-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Media tile 
</p><fig id="GUID-0CB27372-E250-4B7F-8E0D-4C0626327D01" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-C1B33CE1-0E3B-4B8A-AEC1-B9B7BF1AD4FB-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-C1B33CE1-0E3B-4B8A-AEC1-B9B7BF1AD4FB-low.png"/></fig></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Close the drawer to remove this tile. 
</p><fig id="GUID-3C590ED5-94B3-4E5F-BD1D-F712A1ABDBF1" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-DC12FB96-5996-45E9-B8F0-6448E2B46E37-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-DC12FB96-5996-45E9-B8F0-6448E2B46E37-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Tools tile 
</p><fig id="GUID-290B6012-4CBC-4052-9E75-86EC68340AAD" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-570F9D22-E4EB-4E14-A534-7F6F581E757D-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-570F9D22-E4EB-4E14-A534-7F6F581E757D-low.png"/></fig></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Following initialization, the maintenance setting is found to be incorrect. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Prior to handing over the machine to the customer after installation, initiate the periodic maintenance, ensuring that the automatic nozzle optimization is turned off. 
</p><fig id="GUID-E3CD48BA-C176-4D10-974D-027FF2827A3B" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-26C3E3BE-3AF7-42D7-8FE8-012D7852BBBC-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-26C3E3BE-3AF7-42D7-8FE8-012D7852BBBC-low.png"/></fig></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-79AB074B-DA4A-4814-BA62-1CB71234DBA1" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Starting and resuming the wizard</title><p class="- topic/p "> Upon restarting the system using either the main switch or the restart button within the system management settings, the wizard will automatically appear. 
</p><table id="GUID-97ECE09A-696A-4D6F-B45B-897FF9144F1C" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Starting situation 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Resulting UI 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Set the main switch to 1 
</p><fig id="GUID-283D0A52-EB29-44F9-B40B-ACBB8080DD57" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-0D3A44E1-F669-4D4C-AB30-645050D7C6DE-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-0D3A44E1-F669-4D4C-AB30-645050D7C6DE-low.png"/></fig></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The controller will boot and automatically start the wizard. 
</p><fig id="GUID-AE3A69ED-27ED-4F09-942F-00DAC378B2D6" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-11826956-546E-443A-8EEA-A2E71CB087D5-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-11826956-546E-443A-8EEA-A2E71CB087D5-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Press the Restart button via the System tile in the Power management section. 
</p><fig id="GUID-B4656EF3-75A7-453D-B177-7EED2BC828CE" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-DDA605DF-FF5E-40C5-91AF-E6C659456902-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-DDA605DF-FF5E-40C5-91AF-E6C659456902-low.png"/></fig></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> The restart will start the controller and automatically show the wizard. 
</p><fig id="GUID-FC67E3B4-3F55-4B72-90F6-3D924D573263" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-11826956-546E-443A-8EEA-A2E71CB087D5-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-11826956-546E-443A-8EEA-A2E71CB087D5-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> When pressing the restart button in an error view 
</p><fig id="GUID-93624CFD-A5A0-443B-97C9-E1B153D5D40A" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-15B34B7A-4FAF-4D9D-B757-01F8F7F8959E-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-15B34B7A-4FAF-4D9D-B757-01F8F7F8959E-low.png"/></fig></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> The is wizard is not started automatically. It needs to be started manually 
</p><fig id="GUID-F1C5D1DA-5175-45B9-A8FE-FBFFDF60E9F9" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-A9D50A44-750A-449E-853F-F8F7A2B68740-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-A9D50A44-750A-449E-853F-F8F7A2B68740-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Exit the wizard via pressing the cancel button 
</p><fig id="GUID-8B0FC387-99B7-4D35-AE23-D76285A49C13" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-80AA81BC-FCCF-4BC1-BF80-A9914B2F4B75-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-80AA81BC-FCCF-4BC1-BF80-A9914B2F4B75-low.png"/></fig></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> In the normal UI a red Tools tile is visible. 
</p><fig id="GUID-3FCAABC2-9585-45A0-8522-0D266C6BD2EA" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-E1BB05D4-DA90-4E8E-97E6-2960972D45F0-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-E1BB05D4-DA90-4E8E-97E6-2960972D45F0-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The wizard section can be found in the tools tile. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Press the tools tile button 
</p><fig id="GUID-CCEF93F2-AAD4-463E-95AB-B955B6CBC1CE" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-383F70C9-947D-4E19-BD1C-BB33AC7DFE56-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-383F70C9-947D-4E19-BD1C-BB33AC7DFE56-low.png"/></fig></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">At the bottom of the actions in the tools tile a section Resume the installation wizard is shown. 
</p><fig id="GUID-AEB36FC5-1778-466D-BFCE-3681C15EC27A" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-DDE9EC81-72E3-406B-86A9-68DAE6539C91-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-DDE9EC81-72E3-406B-86A9-68DAE6539C91-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> The wizard is resumed by pressing the Resume button in the Resume the installation wizard section. 
</p><fig id="GUID-B1E678FF-4976-4718-86B8-0935847B64CA" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-2BEF6A12-C06F-4772-B0EC-76C07F22FD3E-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-2BEF6A12-C06F-4772-B0EC-76C07F22FD3E-low.png"/></fig></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> The wizard is shown again. The progress indication of the steps can differ every time the wizard is started. 
</p><fig id="GUID-9DC65C87-6151-4AD1-A389-1D5844633CF2" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-740D8DBA-12F2-4507-B1E1-BCB7AEA309AE-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-740D8DBA-12F2-4507-B1E1-BCB7AEA309AE-low.png"/></fig></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-0F466EFA-F27D-47BC-92C1-FCC70D8E01E9" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Exceptions in starting the wizard</title><p class="- topic/p ">If the machine was initiated in Zero SDS mode for analysis, pressing the resume button in the Tools tile won't trigger the wizard. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> To address this, the system must be restarted through the System tile in the power management section. 
</p></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-7D3F358C-1AB9-4A5D-9B0E-C75D689F152E.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Installation</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
</task>